title: Paul McCartney - 2013-07-16 - Miller Park, Milwaukee, WI, USA
description:
<a href="http://veryrare.org" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">http://veryrare.org</a>

Paul McCartney
July 16, 2013
Miller Park
Milwaukee, Wisconsin

Edirol R09H -> AUDACITY -> Amplify -> DIME

My first Macca concert and probably the greatest experience of my life.  The Beatles were the first band I got into, and I've been a fan for 15 years or so, since I was a kid.  I was in Section E, Row 17, seat 3, right by the aile.  I had a great view, and I think the recording came out pretty good.  This is one of better recordings (if that means anything).  The acoustic songs are a big quiet, and there's some minor yelling/clapping, but my "neighbors" were mostly quiet throughout the show.  I hope Paul does more US touring next year, I would love to see him again.  It was hot and nasty in Milwaukee and Paul was sweating a lot, his voice had some rough spots, but, whatever, great show.
